Job Description:
Locations:

Charlotte, NC




The Business Analyst should have at least 3-5 years of experience. Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:




Working constructively with project teams;
Providing coaching and guidance in the realm of processes; working as a thought-leader for business processes and implementation;
Performing root-cause analysis;
Developing precise management plans for each project;
Performing continuous process improvement;
Facilitation of work-package prioritization;
Documenting business requirements and planning of each project;
Interdepartmental, stakeholder, and upper management communication;
Establishing meaning and lasting relationships with project partners for optimized systems integration;
Dashboard creation and visualization to understand project performance;
Project management assistance.

Business analysts should also have some experience in forecasting, critical path method schedule management, and risk management. Heavy industrial, construction, and/or utility and manufacturing experience is preferred.
